---
description: Rust/Tauri backend boundaries and privacy guardrails
globs:
  - src-tauri/**
alwaysApply: false
---

- Preserve Tauri v2 + Rust backend architecture.
- Keep provider boundaries explicit (OpenAI-compatible/OpenRouter, Deepgram).
- Preserve WorkConversation and Interview Mode behavior contracts.
- Do not log API keys, bearer tokens, credential values, raw transcripts, raw prompts, or provider response bodies.
- If `Cargo.toml` or Rust dependency graph changed, run `pnpm rust:deps`.
- Keep schema and IPC changes backward-safe and covered by tests/checks.